President Trump made remarks to the press before departing to visit Dayton, Ohio, and El Paso, Texas, in the wake of recent mass shootings. He addressed criticism that his rhetoric has emboldened white nationalists, saying that his critics are political people looking for gain. He also agreed with Senator Ted Cruz that both sides of the political aisle need to tone down the rhetoric. Regarding gun control, the President expressed support for background checks but stated that there is no political appetite for banning assault rifles. He also discussed the trade war with China, expressing confidence that the market reaction is anticipated and that the US is making headway in negotiations. The President defended his stance on illegal immigration, saying that it is a terrible thing for the country and that legal immigration is preferred. He also responded to comments by Joe Biden, calling him "a pretty incompetent guy."